<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 11:46PM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Treacherous Road Conditions into Saturday Morning...
Snowfall Friday evening of 1/2 to 1 inch and falling temperatures
have led to snow and ice covered roadways. With temperatures
falling into the single digits overnight, roadways will continue
to be treacherous into Saturday morning. In addition, be alert for
blowing and drifting of snow especially in open areas. Northwest
winds will continue to gust up to 40 mph, gradually diminishing
towards morning.
Black ice will cause roads, bridges and overpasses to become
slick and dangerous. Slow down and be prepared for sudden loss of
traction.</description>
